China’s Beidahuang to Buy Overseas Plantations, Magazine Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-08T05:38:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/china-s-beidahuang-to-buy-overseas-plantations-magazine-says.html
  China ’s Heilongjiang Beidahuang
Nongken Group Co. plans to invest overseas in agricultural
projects this year, including plantation purchases, China
Entrepreneur Magazine reported, citing Chairman Sui Fengfu.  Beidahuang Group will acquire 3 million mu (200,000
hectares) of land and possible locations include Russia, the  Philippines , Brazil,  Argentina , Australia, Zimbabwe and
Venezuela, the magazine said on its website yesterday, citing
Sui, who is a Heilongjiang provincial delegate to the National
People’s Congress.  Beidahuang Group will also build palm oil processing plants
and grain logistics facilities overseas, Sui was cited by the
magazine as saying, without giving details of the investments.  State-owned Beidahuang Group operates China’s biggest
farming business and its subsidiaries include the soybean
crusher JiuSan Oil & Fat Co., according to its website.
Heilongjiang is China’s biggest producer of soybeans.  --William Bi. Editor: James Poole  To contact the reporter on this story:
